1
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,720
TOMAR-RE:
Billions of years ago...

2
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:37,940
a race of immortals harnessed
the most powerful force in existence:

3
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:41,560
The emerald energy of willpower.

4
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:44,150
These immortals,
the Guardians of the Universe...

5
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:47,440
.-built a world from where they could
watch over all of existence:

6
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,000
The planet Oa.

7
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:54,660
They divided the universe
into 3600 sectors.

8
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:59,960
A ring powered by the energy of will was
sent to every sector to select a recruit.

9
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:05,350
In order to be chosen by the ring,
it was said one must be without fear.

10
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:08,670
Together, these 3600 recruits...

11
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:14,100
.. formed the intergalactic peacekeepers
known as the Green Lantern Corps.

12
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,790
Of all the threats the Corps
ever faced...

13
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:29,710
..the gravest was an entity of fear
known as Parallax.

14
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:32,530
Only the legendary Green Lantern
Abin Sur...

15
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:35,770
Â«was capable of capturing
and imprisoning this beast...

16
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:39,509
.-Which he did
on the lost planet of Ryut.

17
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:02,310
COMMANDER [IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]:

18
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:30,010
[ALL YELLING]

19
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:38,210
[ALL GRUNTING]

20
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,930
[ALL GASPING]

21
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:01,890
[ALL YELLING]

22
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,460
You are afraid.

23
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:08,530
Good.

24
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:11,450
[ROARS]

25
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:17,570
[ALL SCREAMING]

26
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,739
[ROARS]

27
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:35,270
[BEEPING]

28
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:46,190
Sinestro, I'm traveling at maximum
velocity. Tell Fentara I should--

29
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,110
Fentara is dead.

30
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,440
The planet's inhabitants?

31
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,870
Your mission to evacuate them
is no longer necessary.

32
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:57,440
It's just as it was on Talok.

33
00:04:58,080 --> 00:05:00,609
Every life form destroyed
and their essence absorbed.

34
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,970
Traces of yellow power everywhere.

35
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,480
And the Guardians?

36
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,870
The Guardians are silent.

37
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,050
I've demanded an audience with them.

38
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:14,460
[RING BEEPING]

39
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,680
PARALLAX:
Abin Sur.

40
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:24,410
[ABIN SUR GRUNTING]

41
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,600
[PARALLAX GROWLING]

42
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,479
[PARALLAX GROWLS]

43
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,370
[PANTING]

44
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:10,860
ABIN SUR:
I'm badly wounded.

45
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:15,380
Heading to the nearest inhabited planet
for the selection process.

46
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,160
Tell the Guardians it's Parallax.

47
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,030
[BOTH GRUNT]

48
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,060
[CLOCK CLICKS]

49
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,700
No. No.

50
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:44,050
Sorry, I gotta run.
Make yourself at home, okay?

51
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,950
There's, uh, water in the tap.

52
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,290
HAL:
No!

53
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,070
Yup.

54
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,890
[TRUCK HORN HONKING]

55
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,320
Asshole.

56
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,970
MAN:
The Ferris Sabre Ill is state-of-the-art...

57
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,580
.. of artificial-intelligence
fighter planes.

58
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:29,270
It has all of the flying and combat
capability of a human pilot...

59
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:32,550
.. but with none of the human error
that comes with it.

60
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:35,599
Carl isn't just blowing smoke
to get a contract, general.

61
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,800
Your staff, these contractors,
my Office...

62
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,200
.. we've all been part of this
from the ground up.

63
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,200
Well, l appreciate that, senator.

64
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,310
HAMMOND:
But today the rubber meets the road.

65
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,300
We have a simulated
combat situation.

66
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:49,170
Two Sabres against
Carl's two best pilots.

67
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,390
[CAR HORN HONKING]

68
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:05,090
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

69
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,990
Carol. Was gonna do a little flying today.
What do you think?

70
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,530
I think you're late.

71
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,590
Yes, but that's only because I slept in.

72
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,680
l used to sleep in. Then I turned 11.

73
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,690
Let me give you a little heads-up.

74
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:18,920
I've gone up against these Sabres
all week and they smoked me every time.

75
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:22,320
There isn't anything you can do that
they can't do better, faster...

76
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,810
..and without disappointing women
everywhere.

77
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,240
I, uh, think we both know
that's not true.

78
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:30,560
This is exactly why I didn't want you
for this. My father did.

79
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,310
I would've gone with Jensen.

80
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:35,730
I'd have too, but unfortunately
he's busy not being good enough.

81
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,620
At least he shows up.

82
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,220
Hal...

83
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:41,209
..this test today, it's important.

84
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,990
I'm gonna make you look good up there.
Don't worry, okay?

85
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:47,530
Now let's get these pants off
and fly some planes.

86
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,490
Highball, weapon check now.

87
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:53,920
Roger that.

88
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,750
TOM: Good morning, Mr. Ferris.
CARL: Morning, everybody.

89
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,470
Gentlemen.

90
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:05,500
-We about ready, Tom?
-Yes, Mr. Ferris. We are go for test.

91
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,650
Sapphire, cleared weapons hot
at the merge.

92
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,330
Ferris Test, Sapphire.
Weapons are hot.

93
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,310
Fly safe, Highball.

94
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,430
HAL:
Um, no.

95
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,459
Goddamn it! Tom, what the hell
you feed those things?

96
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,390
F-35s, what else?

97
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,630
[CARL CHUCKLING]

98
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,110
HAL [OVER RADIO]:
Wakey, wakey, Sapphire.

99
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,160
You got a shot,
now would be a great time.

100
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:44,020
Easy, Highball. Just lining it up.

101
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,910
[BEEPING]

102
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,569
There's no way
we're taking these out solo.

103
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,890
Get over here.
Let's figure something out.

104
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,330
CAROL [OVER RADIO]:
On my way, Highball.

105
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,580
HAL:
Now stay right there and look real pretty.

106
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:23,420
[GRUNTING]

107
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:27,150
[BEEPING]

108
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,870
[GRUNTS]

109
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,270
Highball, did you just use your wingman
as a decoy?

110
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,880
[LAUGHING]

111
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:01,140
Highball, those Sabres headed up your 6
can fly anywhere you can.

112
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,370
Then let's go somewhere I can't fly.

113
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,120
What the hell is he up to?

114
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,710
Coffin corner.

115
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:15,070
Highball, rules of engagement
set ceiling at 50,000 feet.

116
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:18,449
HAL: Yeah, because the Sabres will stall
if they go any higher, right, Tom?

117
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,010
And so will you.

118
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:27,880
COMPUTER:
Compressor stall. Compressor stall.

119
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,260
[ALARM BLARING]

120
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,350
[GASPS]

121
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,840
[PANTING]

122
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,980
[BEEPING]

123
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:00,930
[BEEPING]

124
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,449
Yes!

125
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:09,540
[TOM CLEARS THROAT]

126
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,770
Um, I mean, damn it, Hal.

127
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,520
Your boy certainly
takes his job seriously.

128
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,050
TOM [OVER RADIO]:
Ailerons, Hal. Side to side.

129
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,310
I got it.

130
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,880
[ALARM BLARING]

131
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:25,550
MARTIN:
Hal.

132
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:32,150
Keep it warm for me.

133
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,780
TECHNICIAN:
Going through 25,000.

134
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,080
Hey, you okay, Highball?

135
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,750
Yeah, just taking my victory lap.

136
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,720
[GRUNTING]

137
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:50,550
TECHNICIAN: Going through 20,000.
-Okay, Highball, give me some roll.

138
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:57,810
[CHEERS]

139
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,170
Yeah, Dad!

140
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,710
TOM:
Hal, do you read me?

141
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,900
[GASPS]

142
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:13,720
TOM: Highball, you're approaching
minimum ejection altitude.

143
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:21,250
Highball, you're below 10,000 AGL.
Spin is unrecoverable.

144
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,820
Eject, eject, eject!

145
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,870
You're not scared, are you, Dad?

146
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,709
Let's just say it's my job not to be.

147
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,670
HAL:
Dad!

148
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,360
Dad!

149
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:43,230
[GRUNTS]

150
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,310
[GRUNTING]

151
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:52,770
[GASPING]

152
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,040
You stupid son of a bitch. You--

153
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,120
CARL:
Stand down, Bob. It doesn't matter now.

154
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:05,500
It does matter.

155
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:08,260
Never mind that you crashed
a brand-new F-35.

156
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:11,180
You broke the rules of engagement.
You sacrificed your wingman.

157
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:13,890
And you blew the contract
this company was depending on.

158
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:16,010
I'm sorry.
I thought this was a dogfight.

159
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,500
I was under the impression
the objective was to win.

160
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:21,560
No, the objective was to show
what the Sabres could do in combat.

161
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,570
And in combat,
no pilot is gonna crater his own plane.

162
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:26,550
I did.

163
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:29,140
Now you know you gotta
boost the ceiling.

164
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:30,850
I showed you what they can't do.

165
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,450
You didn't have to make that point
in front of Air Force Acquisitions.

166
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:34,969
That's enough, Carol.

167
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:40,140
Since I'm gonna have to lay off most of
my company anyway, you're fired, Hal.

168
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:41,700
It's too late. I quit.

169
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,400
CAROL:
He's not fired and you don't quit.

170
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,930
You're grounded,
pending the results of an investigation.

171
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,810
Watch your back.

172
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,430
That's impossible, Bob.

173
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:05,350
-Tell me what happened.
-Controls locked up.

174
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:08,640
Don't give me that, Hal. You had
a window when you could've recovered.

175
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,500
Did you choke?

176
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:12,630
You wouldn't be the first,
but I need to know.

177
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:15,319
My controls locked up.
What the hell is all this, anyway?

178
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,060
What's with the ridiculous suit?

179
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:20,560
-I know your dad's been bucking for you--
-The merits of my career choices--

180
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:24,709
You're a pilot, and a good one.
Giving that up to fly a desk is bullshit.

181
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,480
like it and I'm good at it.

182
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,920
Doesn't mean I'll never get in a cockpit
again. It isn't one way or the other.

183
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:33,400
That's the way a child looks at things,
and we aren't children anymore.

184
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:36,569
At least....

185
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:43,240
I just don't wanna see
someone I care about getting hurt.

186
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,060
Least of all you.

187
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:12,290
[GRUNTING]

188
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:24,650
Choose well.

189
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,490
[THE ROSES' "FANCY WOMEN"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

190
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,640
[ENGINE STOPS]

191
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:43,490
[CHILDREN CHATTERING]

192
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:50,710
A test pilot's daring maneuvers
almost ended in tragedy.

193
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:55,080
Witnesses say pilot Hal Jordan
ejected at the last possible second...

194
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,510
.. before his jet crashed
in the open desert.

195
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:59,530
He's the son of the late
Martin Jordan...

196
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:02,479
..Who was killed in his own
ill-fated test flight back in 1993.

197
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,140
We are told that Hal Jordan
is doing fine right now...

198
00:17:05,599 --> 00:17:07,990
.. though we have yet to hear
an official statement.

199
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,349
Hey, guys.

200
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:12,660
HEBERT: The incident has been a blow
to a new high-tech aircraft program....

201
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,430
JACK:
Hey. How was work?

202
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,930
Oh. It was amazing, Jack.
Thank you for asking. Hey, Janice.

203
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:20,030
Just help me out here, because
I'm really trying to understand this.

204
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,139
-Mm-hm.
-Do you wanna be like him so bad?

205
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,379
-You just assume it's my fault.
-I talked to Carl.

206
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,619
-Oh. Heh, heh.
-You pushed the plane past its limits--

207
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:29,389
That's my job. It was an accident.
Everybody walked away.

208
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:32,830
Like your motorcycle accident
that put you in the hospital for a month?

209
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:35,680
I miss all this quality family time.
Good talk, Jack.

210
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,970
JACK: God.
JANICE: Jack, come on.

211
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:40,980
JIM:
You okay?

212
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,149
Where's Jason?

213
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:45,480
In his room.

214
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,100
Why?

215
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:49,909
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

216
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,280
HAL:
Hey, it's Uncle Hal.

217
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:53,469
What's up there, ace?

218
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,920
This is the worst 11th birthday party
I've ever been to.

219
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:59,550
No dancing girls?
What's going on--? Hey.

220
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:02,050
Hey.

221
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,450
I'm fine.

222
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:06,760
I guess I got a little freaked out
or something.

223
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,780
It happens.

224
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,070
Not to you.

225
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:11,860
Look...

226
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:14,560
..you don't have anything
to worry about.

227
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:15,830
You wanna know why?

228
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:19,379
Yeah, I may be a total screw-up
in every other part of my life...

229
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:23,370
.. but the one thing I do know
how to do is fly.

230
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:29,540
Hey, got you something, birthday boy.
Wrapped it myself.

231
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,980
Cool. It's an X-1, right?

232
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,959
It's a Starfighter.
My dad gave me that.

233
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:41,880
Let's put it up.

234
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,570
What happened today?

235
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,320
I mean, when you crashed.

236
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,290
HAL:
Not really sure, exactly.

237
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:52,639
Were you scared?

238
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:56,280
It's my job not to be.

239
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:01,360
You know, you're totally missing
your super-lame birthday party.

240
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:04,940
Beat it. Go, go, go!

241
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:09,340
I'm glad you're okay.

242
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:13,430
Me too, ace.

243
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:27,070
[GRUNTING]

244
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:28,409
Get off! No!

245
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,760
Aah! No!

246
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:35,719
[YELLING]

247
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:41,850
[GRUNTS]

248
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:44,690
[PANTING]

249
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:13,510
[GRUNTING]

250
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:31,890
[HAL GRUNTS]

251
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,160
HAL:
