00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:47,420
This planet has been our home
for countless millennia.

513
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:50,530
It was created for us
by the Guardians.

514
00:40:51,040 --> 00:40:52,440
Guardians?

515
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,310
There stands their Citadel.

516
00:40:55,120 --> 00:40:57,790
They are immortals,
among the most ancient of races.

517
00:40:58,320 --> 00:41:01,900
They made all you see and are
responsible for all we are and do.

518
00:41:03,120 --> 00:41:05,150
Since time immemorial,
the Green Lantern Corps...

519
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:08,060
..has served as the keepers of peace,
order and justice...

520
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:10,029
.. throughout the universe.

521
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:13,870
To be chosen to join its ranks
is the highest of honors...

522
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:16,440
..and the greatest of responsibilities.

523
00:41:16,880 --> 00:41:18,980
Yeah. Yeah, that part I heard about.

524
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:21,040
We're going to fly now.

525
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,150
-Fly?
-Absolutely.

526
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:27,880
All right.

527
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,480
I can do that.

528
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:36,750
Join me.

529
00:41:38,520 --> 00:41:40,100
I can do that.

530
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:49,530
[HAL YELLING]

531
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:51,540
[HAL LAUGHING]

532
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:53,320
Yeah!

533
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:55,350
Whoa!

534
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:57,470
Whoa!

535
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:03,020
[HAL CHUCKLING]

536
00:42:27,480 --> 00:42:28,670
What is that?

537
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:31,460
TOMAR-RE: It's the energy that's
generated from the Central Battery.

538
00:42:31,960 --> 00:42:34,910
Its power comes from the will
of every living creature in the universe.

539
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:39,899
It, in turn, charges your lantern,
which, in turn, charges your ring.

540
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:43,520
Even your suit is comprised
entirely of energy.

541
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:45,440
What's with all the green?

542
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:46,990
Green is the color of will.

543
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:48,620
The Guardians harnessed will...

544
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:51,730
.. because it's the strongest
source of energy in the universe.

545
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:57,560
HAL:
There's so many.

546
00:42:57,920 --> 00:43:00,970
TOMAR-RE: The stars you can see from
your home planet on the clearest night...

547
00:43:01,560 --> 00:43:03,279
.-your sector is a thousand
times larger.

548
00:43:04,840 --> 00:43:08,980
And 3600 Lanterns,
each with a sector just as vast.

549
00:43:09,720 --> 00:43:12,250
[ALL CHATTERING
IN ALIEN LANGUAGES]

550
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:35,400
Lanterns, I've called you here
to this unprecedented gathering...

551
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:38,730
.. because we face
an unprecedented danger.

552
00:43:40,680 --> 00:43:44,370
Our four Lantern brothers
were killed by an enemy called Parallax.

553
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:48,880
An enemy we don't yet
fully understand.

554
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:53,649
We do know it's powerful enough
to destroy entire civilizations.

555
00:43:55,520 --> 00:43:58,850
Powerful enough
to defeat even Abin Sur...

556
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:01,550
.our finest warrior...

557
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:04,990
..wWhose light can never be replaced.

558
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:07,470
[ALL MURMURING
IN ALIEN LANGUAGES]

559
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:13,280
SINESTRO: The Guardians have charged
me to lead a squadron of Lanterns...

560
00:44:13,840 --> 00:44:15,310
..in an assault on Parallax.

561
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:18,799
We will seek out and find this enemy.

562
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:22,460
And we will destroy it.

563
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:26,590
Alone, we are now vulnerable.

564
00:44:27,280 --> 00:44:30,230
United, we are still invincible.

565
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:32,900
We have never been defeated.

566
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:35,100
Will we be defeated now?

567
00:44:35,480 --> 00:44:36,460
ALL:
No!

568
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:41,350
SINESTRO: It was for this moment
that we were created.

569
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:44,670
But I don't need to tell you your duty.

570
00:44:45,200 --> 00:44:47,730
I don't need to tell you who we are.

571
00:44:48,240 --> 00:44:50,339
[GUARDIAN SHOUTING
IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

572
00:44:51,520 --> 00:44:54,750
LANTERNS [CHANTING]:
We are the Corps! We are the Corps!

573
00:44:56,080 --> 00:44:59,770
We are the Corps! We are the Corps!

574
00:45:03,880 --> 00:45:06,790
TOMAR-RE:
Your will turns thought into reality.

575
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:09,930
To master the ring,
you must learn to focus your will...

576
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:12,960
..and create what you see
in your mind.

577
00:45:16,480 --> 00:45:18,650
The ring's limits
are only what you can imagine.

578
00:45:24,080 --> 00:45:25,200
Do that again.

579
00:45:25,520 --> 00:45:26,570
Now you try.

580
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:29,860
Concentrate.

581
00:45:33,080 --> 00:45:33,950
[BLows]

582
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:45,420
[RING BEEPING]

583
00:45:45,720 --> 00:45:48,419
The ring will inform you
where there is an imminent threat.

584
00:45:49,440 --> 00:45:51,610
[GRUNTING]

585
00:45:52,080 --> 00:45:54,470
TOMAR-RE:
This particular threatâs name is Kilowog.

586
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:57,060
He'll be your combat training officer.

587
00:45:57,680 --> 00:46:01,009
HAL: Whoa!
-Never let your guard down, poozer.

588
00:46:01,920 --> 00:46:03,740
Welcome to Ring Slinging 101.

589
00:46:04,160 --> 00:46:05,490
Or as I like to call it:

590
00:46:05,840 --> 00:46:08,260
The worst day of your worthless life.

591
00:46:11,040 --> 00:46:13,529
The human.
Ain't never seen one before.

592
00:46:14,040 --> 00:46:15,930
[KILOWOG SNIFFS THEN SNORTS]

593
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:18,010
-You smell funny.
-Ugh.

594
00:46:18,720 --> 00:46:19,589
I smell funny?

595
00:46:19,880 --> 00:46:23,040
Yeah, I heard about humans.
Think you're the center of the universe.

596
00:46:23,800 --> 00:46:26,750
You want to be a Lantern?
You gotta commit to the Corps.

597
00:46:29,720 --> 00:46:31,790
All right, poozer.
Let's see what you've got.

598
00:46:35,400 --> 00:46:37,430
[GRUNTING]

599
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:47,750
Your constructs are only gonna be
as strong as your will.

600
00:46:48,320 --> 00:46:49,580
And your will is pathetic.

601
00:46:54,400 --> 00:46:56,260
I'm gonna work you
and I'm gonna hit you...

602
00:46:56,680 --> 00:46:59,589
.-until your will is strong enough
to be worthy of the Corps.

603
00:47:00,160 --> 00:47:03,109
[BOTH GRUNTING]

604
00:47:12,480 --> 00:47:13,600
KILOWOG:
Next lesson.

605
00:47:16,640 --> 00:47:18,460
Ha, ha. Feel that?

606
00:47:18,880 --> 00:47:21,090
It's the gravitational pull
of your average sun.

607
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:24,470
Makes flying through space
very dangerous.

608
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:27,710
The bigger you are,
the quicker you burn.

609
00:47:30,520 --> 00:47:32,240
Gravity's a bitch.

610
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:36,980
Here, let me help you.

611
00:47:39,840 --> 00:47:43,910
Remember, your enemy,
he's not gonna play fair.

612
00:47:50,720 --> 00:47:53,209
Well, that's good advice.
Thanks, gorgeous.

613
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:54,950
SINESTRO:
So...

614
00:47:56,600 --> 00:47:58,110
Â«this is the human.

615
00:47:59,040 --> 00:48:01,140
When I learned Abin Sur's ring
had chosen you...

616
00:48:01,600 --> 00:48:02,860
..[ said there had to be a mistake.

617
00:48:03,200 --> 00:48:05,160
[KILOWOG GROANING]

618
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:07,670
I see nothing to change my mind.

619
00:48:08,560 --> 00:48:10,000
I'll take it from here, Kilowog.

620
00:48:12,280 --> 00:48:14,140
The Corps is only as strong
as its weakest link.

621
00:48:15,040 --> 00:48:17,210
And I will tolerate no weak links.

622
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,160
You understand me?

623
00:48:21,080 --> 00:48:23,330
Are you afraid, human?

624
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:27,290
Are you afraid?

625
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:28,470
Don't.

626
00:48:28,760 --> 00:48:29,670
[CHUCKLES]

627
00:48:30,640 --> 00:48:32,080
Don't do that.

628
00:48:36,520 --> 00:48:37,600
Shall we?

629
00:48:40,480 --> 00:48:41,600
Sure.

630
00:48:42,760 --> 00:48:44,200
A sword?

631
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:46,100
How human.

632
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:49,530
[BOTH GRUNTING]

633
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:58,140
I do believe I smell fear.

634
00:48:59,840 --> 00:49:01,000
[YELLS]

635
00:49:02,200 --> 00:49:03,140
[PANTING]

636
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:05,050
I'm a Green Lantern.

637
00:49:07,280 --> 00:49:08,960
I fear nothing.

638
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:12,950
Fear is the enemy of will.

639
00:49:13,360 --> 00:49:14,900
Will is what makes you take action.

640
00:49:18,520 --> 00:49:21,570
Fear is what stops you
and makes you weak.

641
00:49:27,600 --> 00:49:29,279
Makes your constructs feeble.

642
00:49:39,360 --> 00:49:41,960
You must ignore your fear.
When you're afraid, you can't act.

643
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:45,460
When you can't act, you can't defend.
If you can't defend, you die.

644
00:49:50,720 --> 00:49:52,399
You reek of fear, Hal Jordan.

645
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:54,600
Abin Sur was a great warrior.

646
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:56,750
My mentor.

647
00:49:57,240 --> 00:49:58,569
My friend.

648
00:49:59,320 --> 00:50:02,760
You insult his memory
by wearing his ring.

649
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:23,370
I'm done. He's right. I'm only human.
We're not ready to defend the universe.

650
00:50:23,960 --> 00:50:26,520
A few days ago, we thought we were
the only ones in the universe.

651
00:50:27,040 --> 00:50:30,130
The ring chose you. It wouldn't have
if it hadn't seen something in you.

652
00:50:30,720 --> 00:50:31,589
Oh, yeah?

653
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:33,740
Something you yourself don't yet see.

654
00:50:34,160 --> 00:50:35,770
The ring never makes a mistake.

655
00:50:37,080 --> 00:50:38,380
This time it did.

656
00:51:01,680 --> 00:51:02,690
[SIGHS]

657
00:51:24,760 --> 00:51:28,200
HECTOR: --that until recently, we didn't
realize that many of these little critters...

658
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:31,470
..that we've been calling bacteria
weren't bacteria at all.

659
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:36,070
They were an entirely different type
of primitive prokaryotic cell.

660
00:51:36,800 --> 00:51:40,130
These little buggers, called archaeans,
are still poorly understood.

661
00:51:40,760 --> 00:51:42,510
[STUDENTS THINKING INDISTINCTLY]

662
00:51:43,240 --> 00:51:44,220
Um....

663
00:51:44,520 --> 00:51:47,080
But might turn out to be
different from bacteria--

664
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:50,130
[STUDENTS THINKING INDISTINCTLY]

665
00:51:50,640 --> 00:51:54,190
But might turn out to be as different
from bacteria as bacteria is from us.

666
00:51:54,840 --> 00:51:55,920
Some call them extremophiles...

667
00:51:56,240 --> 00:51:57,149
[MICHAEL YAWNS]

668
00:51:57,440 --> 00:52:00,350
.. because they live in the most extreme
environments on Earth, such as...

669
00:52:00,920 --> 00:52:02,710
MICHAEL [THINKING]:
God, he's so boring.

670
00:52:03,120 --> 00:52:04,520
..the boiling waters of a geyser.

671
00:52:04,880 --> 00:52:06,070
MICHAEL [THINKING]:
What a loser.

672
00:52:07,200 --> 00:52:08,710
-Michael!
-Huh?

673
00:52:09,840 --> 00:52:10,710
What did you say?

674
00:52:11,680 --> 00:52:12,660
I didn't say anything.

675
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:17,170
Did you just call me a loser?

676
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:19,270
MICHAEL [THINKING]:
What kind of freak is this guy?

677
00:52:19,680 --> 00:52:21,049
"Freak"?!

678
00:52:22,080 --> 00:52:23,160
[SCOFFS]

679
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:28,240
[MICHAEL YELLS THEN GRUNTS]

680
00:52:28,640 --> 00:52:29,799
[STUDENTS GASPING
AND SCREAMING]

681
00:52:30,120 --> 00:52:32,609
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

682
00:52:39,040 --> 00:52:40,440
Class dismissed.

683
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:06,740
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

684
00:53:21,280 --> 00:53:22,820
So how you been?

685
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:24,910
Been a while.

686
00:53:26,320 --> 00:53:28,920
So you had a rough night last night.
Did you get her name, huh?

687
00:53:29,440 --> 00:53:31,720
[BOTH LAUGHING]

688
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:34,299
You need to get some sleep, son.

689
00:53:35,120 --> 00:53:37,650
-Have a seat.
-What can I do for you, Dad?

690
00:53:38,160 --> 00:53:40,190
Well, actually, you've already done it.

691
00:53:41,040 --> 00:53:42,509
For me and for your country.

692
00:53:43,200 --> 00:53:44,460
What are you talking about?

693
00:53:44,800 --> 00:53:49,150
I'm talking about you impressing
a whole lot of very important people.

694
00:53:52,000 --> 00:53:53,370
Where did you get that?

695
00:53:53,720 --> 00:53:56,700
I'm on a subcommittee
overseeing the agencies involved.

696
00:53:57,280 --> 00:54:01,490
-Top-secret, of course.
-It was you. That's why they chose me.

697
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:05,700
Because of this, we're gonna be able
to get you a top post on the inside now...

698
00:54:06,320 --> 00:54:07,720
.. helping to oversee the operation.

699
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:11,940
There are scientists
that worked their whole lives for this.

700
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:14,319
-Mm-hm.
-People more qualified.

701
00:54:14,720 --> 00:54:15,799
And less connected.

702
00:54:16,120 --> 00:54:19,170
Don't be naive, son.
It's the way the world works.

703
00:54:19,880 --> 00:54:22,720
You have to seize an opportunity
when it presents itself.

704
00:54:25,760 --> 00:54:27,200
HAMMOND [THINKING]:
He'll never get it.

705
00:54:27,560 --> 00:54:28,500
Just wasting his life away.

706
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:29,670
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

707
00:54:29,960 --> 00:54:31,190
What an embarrassment.

708
00:54:33,120 --> 00:54:35,930
Bill! Ha. How are you?

709
00:54:36,480 --> 00:54:37,880
I'm terrific.

710
00:54:38,240 --> 00:54:41,540
No, no, no. Just finishing up a meeting.
Got plenty of time.

711
00:55:04,160 --> 00:55:05,839
[GROWLS]

712
00:55:11,320 --> 00:55:13,850
[GRUNTING]

713
00:55:17,600 --> 00:55:20,130
[ROARING]

714
00:55:30,440 --> 00:55:32,300
[GRUNTING]

715
00:55:34,200 --> 00:55:36,899
[BOTH SCREAMING]

716
00:55:38,880 --> 00:55:40,600
SINESTRO:
With my own eyes saw this creature...

717
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:42,720
induce fear in our finest warriors...

718
00:55:43,120 --> 00:55:44,910
..and then feed on that fear.

719
00:55:45,920 --> 00:55:47,110
There's more.

720
00:55:47,440 --> 00:55:50,810
We've tracked its trajectory.
Parallax is headed for Oa.

721
00:55:51,760 --> 00:55:53,720
Never before has an enemy
dared attack us here.

722
00:55:54,160 --> 00:55:56,049
You must tell me what you know.

723
00:55:58,720 --> 00:56:00,750
FIRST GUARDIAN:
Will has always been our sole weapon...

724
00:56:01,200 --> 00:56:03,480
.. against the forces of darkness
in the universe.

725
00:56:04,280 --> 00:56:07,260
But as that power began to seem
insufficient...

726
00:56:07,840 --> 00:56:09,940
..a great debate arose among us.

727
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:12,430
Should we exploit
another source of power...

728
00:56:13,040 --> 00:56:16,410
..one we had long since sworn
should never be used?

729
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:18,700
Fear.

730
00:56:19,040 --> 00:56:22,130
But the power of fear
was too unpredictable.

731
00:56:22,720 --> 00:56:24,970
The chance of corruption too great.

732
00:56:25,440 --> 00:56:27,470
And so we decided against it.

733
00:56:27,920 --> 00:56:31,290
All of us, that is, except one.

734
00:56:32,440 --> 00:56:35,600
Alone, this Guardian
entered the forbidden chamber.

735
00:56:36,200 --> 00:56:39,529
He wanted to prove the light of fear
could be mastered.

736
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:42,549
His intentions were pure...

737
00:56:43,040 --> 00:56:45,640
..but his hopes were naive.

738
00:56:46,800 --> 00:56:49,220
Consumed by the yellow power
of fear...

739
00:56:49,720 --> 00:56:53,549
..the Guardian became the very evil
he had wished to destroy.

740
00:56:54,240 --> 00:56:55,990
He became Parallax.

741
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:05,980
For the universe's safety
and his own...

742
00:57:06,480 --> 00:57:10,060
.-Abin Sur was charged with
imprisoning Parallax in the Lost Sector.

743
00:57:10,720 --> 00:57:11,879
But he escaped.

744
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:15,529
Feeding on the fear of others,
he grew larger, more powerful.

745
00:57:16,160 --> 00:57:17,140
And is now headed here...

746
00:57:17,440 --> 00:57:20,250
..to take his revenge on you
and destroy the Corps.

747
00:57:27,200 --> 00:57:29,020
Then we have no choice.

748
00:57:29,920 --> 00:57:33,080
We must prepare to harness the power
of our enemy and fight fear with fear.

749
00:57:33,680 --> 00:57:36,350
To protect our sectors,
we must be able to defend ourselves.

750
00:57:37,880 --> 00:57:40,200
We must forge a yellow ring.

751
00:57:48,960 --> 00:57:49,830
CREWMAN:
Watch your step.

752
00:57:50,120 --> 00:57:51,490
MAN: Senator.
WOMAN: Senator.

753
00:57:51,840 --> 00:57:54,300
[SINGING]
Don't have to worry about me no more

754
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:57,500
I'm gone

755
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:02,009
I'm gone, I'm gone

756
00:58:04,920 --> 00:58:05,790
TOM:
Hello.

757
00:58:06,080 --> 00:58:07,130
Hi.

758
00:58:07,440 --> 00:58:09,970
[BAND PLAYING "BAREFOOTIN'']

759
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:14,210
SINGER [SINGING]:
Everybody get on your feet

760
00:58:15,680 --> 00:58:17,569
You make me nervous
When you're in your seat

761
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:19,830
Rough night, huh?

762
00:58:21,760 --> 00:58:22,810
Hector.

763
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:25,540
How you doing?
What have you been up to?

764
00:58:25,920 --> 00:58:28,130
-Same old, same old.
